ratings.rComments: Amazing guy and amazing teacher but you have to absolutely give it your all if you wanna do well. He likes to test you on why you do something so make sure you completely understand the idea behind the concept instead of just learning how to do it.

His exams are super hard, our class averages were always failing or even below 50%. His lectures aren't super helpful but he knows what he is talking about. Make sure to really understand all of the homework problems because he likes to put them on quizzes and exams. People told me to take anyone but Hummel, but I think I would have preferred him.

He is an amazing professor; however, the lecture material never coincides with the homework or discussions very well. He lectures at a slower pace than the pace of the material given. So expect  a lot of personal learning and studying.
He's a great teacher. Read the book and do the challenge problems if you want to pass. The exams are hard
He's a great teacher. Read the book and do the challenge problems if you want to pass.

Dr. Decoste is super good with answering your questions even when you go to his office when its not office hours. Make sure to use your resources such as the Chemistry learning center and the teaching assistants. Don't procrastinate until the day before the exam.

I promise you'll regret it someday if you ever skip any of his lectures. I have graduated and moved on from chemistry however that class was hands down the best class of my student career. I'll never forget it. Decoste was the best professor I ever had.
READ THE TEXTBOOK! HE WROTE IT! Show up to class and make sure you are talking to him, he is super helpful if you ask for help, so ask!

Decoste is awesome! His lectures are always entertaining and informative, and he is incredibly helpful in office hours. That said, his classes are tough and he makes you really work for your grade. Difficult, but fair.

Dr. Decoste is a great professor! His lectures is interesting and he'll use demos to grab your attention. He covers everything in the lecture and his explanation is clear. I've never been to his office hours but I heard from my classmates that he's ready to help you with your questions. Midterm exams are hard but final exam is not that hard.

Dr. Decoste will go above and beyond for his students without hesitation. His tests are a bit difficult, but he does cover everything in lecture. As long as you attend lecture and keep up with homework and quizzes, the tests won't be too surprising. Also, the textbook is rarely used.

Dr. Decoste is a great professor! His lectures are fun and he knows how to grab your attention with his demos. He truly is inspirational and even though the course is tough, he's always there to help you if you show that you are interested and willing to put in the work. Don't be intimidated to go to office hours or ask him questions after lecture!
Great lectures, very live with demonstrations. Professor DeCoste emails you back within 2 hours (amazing!) with a clear explanation. Knows the content through and through. Tests are EXTREMELY hard.
Decoste goes above and beyond traditional chemistry teaching methods, but the student must also study in the same way.
The class is really lively with demonstrations, but the tests are super hard

this class is a lot of work. stay on top of your readings, do all your homework and labs on time and you should be okay. Decoste is literally one of the nicest professors you'll ever have. TAKE ADVANTAGE OF HIS OFFICE HOURS. he is so willing to help and breaks things down into the simplest of terms for you. Probably my favorite teacher at U of I.

Best teacher I have had. College chemistry as a freshman is very intimidating. However he is probably the most helpful teacher i have ever had. He has genuine interest in your success. Show interest early on in class. If you care about the class he will care about helping you.

Chem Lab is SO time-consuming for the 1 hour credit. ALWAYS have your lab notebook completely prepared so that you can finish your labs & don't forget to do your IVLs. Luckily, labs are every other week and your grade is curved so don't worry about which TA you get. Decoste prepared helpful video resources for each lab and is good at explaining.

DeCoste is an awesome professor; he made lectures real interesting and he was a pretty funny guy. He is definitely easy to approach and very helpful. I don't remember his exams being hard at all, but rather really easy, compared to Dr. Ray

It's quite obvious that he loves his career, which, I believe, makes him better at it. He does many demonstrations to illustrate the material he's going over. He's always urging people who have trouble to come to office hours or make an appointment- very helpful.
Best professor I have ever had.

Decoste is a fantastic professor. Although his lectures are a bit vague relative to the detail on the exams, he's very helpful in office hours and is always willing to meet outside of his OH's or lecture. I would definitely recommend taking any class with him.

Very enthusiastic and fun! Really wants to teach chemistry and make sure his students understand the fundamentals. Only his first year teaching 104, but did a great job. Most definitely recommend as a chemistry professor.

Haven't had a better professor for any class on campus so far. Don's by far the most enthusiastic, energetic professors on campus, not to mention fun! His demonstrations are like magic.. but when you get down to it, its all chemistry!! A true gem amongst university instructors.

Definitly a class I enjoyed.  He would always do the pop bottle before class and it immediatley got everyones attention.  Funny guy and a great teacher, down to earth + helpful.  The material admittedly is not a cakewalk but he does a great job and TAs were very helpful as well.  If anyone gets BRANDEN ITO as ta you are lucky!!!!!!

DeCoste's test are really difficult.  His lectures will keep you interested for the most part, but to do well on the tests you need to really know what your doing. Practice tests and homework problems will help.

DeCoste was definitely one of the best teachers I have ever had.  Coming into the class I hated chemistry but he was somehow able to get me to look forward to coming to lecture.  Now if that's not incredible I don't know what is.

Dr. DeCoste is an incredible professor. He takes a much more holistic approach to chemistry rather than strictly mathematical. You can learn so much in this class because he encourages you to understand material, not memorize. Overall, PHENOMENAL.

Decoste is a good professor who explains concepts very well. He is currently my best professor, and I don't mind going to his class even though I'm not a big fan of chemistry. His exams are challenging but not impossible, if you go to class and do the homework you'll be fine.

Probably the best professor I have ever had. I would actually look forward to his class because he was so enjoyable to listen to and be around. He loves what he does and loves his students. Our tests were straightforward multiple choice questions and a few difficult free response questions, but nothing too difficult.
Makes class fun
He's one of the best Chem professors

It felt like going back to high school. It feels like you are taught to the exam, which while it gives easy exams, it gives an unsatisfying feeling. People were raving about how great Decoste was which left me feeling a bit underwhelmed when he wasn't better. He's a really fun professor, but his actual teaching isn't anything extraordinary.
Great lectures, always interesting. Take his class and make sure you go, and you'll learn a great deal.

I'm gonna chime in here and agree that he is one of the BEST professors I've ever had. I'm a business major and I was really scared to take this class but he made it so much easier.  Excellent explainer and very helpful
Professor Decoste was the best professor I've ever had.
He explains everything really well. He is clearly passionate about what he teaches. The class is a lot of fun.
Best Chem prof on campus, hands down!

well... after hearing soo much good stuff abou him ... i agree hes a GREAT professor BUT ... he has this thing of not deriving stuff and not teaching WHY something happens .. hes always like "It happens"... personally i like the "derivation" kinda way.. but hes not big on that at ALL.. i'd say professor brubele for 202 was MUCH MUCH better

I loved Decoste. Considering the amount and extent of info learned in 202, He was a magician. He was really helpful in 203 as well, because my TA was a joke. He can clearly explain concepts and is very availible if you need help. He's always around. I don't have his class now, but I still see him strolling by Chem Annex.

He is a very easy to understand professor.  He strives to make sure his students understand the material.  Tests incorporate multiple choice and 2-3 problem questions at the end, which help your understanding of the topics.  Overall a wonderful professor.  I only wish he would go back to teaching CHEM 202 so I could have him next year too!
Very fun prof, does a lot of BOOM heavy demos in class, so you can't nod off. Explains things very well.
A GREAT professor! goes through materials really fast, but just go to office hours. explains materials very well during office hours. exams are very hard. fairly difficult class in general.
Great professor. HE can make esreything seem so eay and understandable but dont be fooled because when the exam comes you will feel like u didnt understand anything. But still a great class.
Really cool professor.  awesome demos, keeps things interesting.  It is a pretty tough class though, no doubt about it.

Awesome guy. If you don't get something during lecture, just go to his office hours. He's extremely helpful.  Lectures are generally fun because he is always doing some experiment or blowing up something...
GREAT!!
awesome professor. Thats it. His exams are very hard but there are sweeeet curves. Very helpful but can go fast in his lectures and lectures are a must attend, or you can be screwed for the exams.
Amazing professor! Interesting lectures, cool demos, clear explanations and good examples. Highly reccommended. LOVE LOVE LOVE
clear, knows how to explain. give examples, fun demos, awesome person!

What to say about him... you have not seen awesome until you see him!  Extremely helpful (I went to his office EVERY WEEK!) and very nice. Tests are equally tough!!! (class averages were usually 50% or so.)
Never seen a professor like him!! he is just the best - halirious, awesome, knows what he is doing and loves chemistry you can tell.. Tests are extremely hard but averages are pretty low anyways.
Just great.
Best demos ever.  Great Great teacher
AWESOME AWESOME AWESOME AWESOME AWESOME PROF EVER!

GREAT PROFESSOR...HARD TESTS..TRICKY TOO.. BUT HOMEWORK AND QUIZES GIVE A GOOD CHANCE TO BRING GRADE UP.. C IS DEFINALTELY THE LEAST GRADE YOU SHOULD GET...TAKE ADVANTAGE OF OFFICE HOURS AND/OR NON-OFFICE HOURS..HE IS AN AWESOME GUY! POSSIBLY THE BEST PROFESSOR I HAVE MET SO FAR IN MY LIFE!

FUNNY - WILL MAKE YOUR DAY! He definately loves chemistry and knows what he is doing.. Extremely helpful..take advantage of office hours.. tests are very hard - STUDY!! Cares about your grades as much as you do so ask him for help (I went to see him every week!)
Don is THE DON OF CHEMISTRY
Don is the chemistry GOD!
Very helpful. Awesome guy.
great!
He's the best!
Best professor I've had so far
Ahhh! And its only the beginning!
he let me switch sections a couple days into the semester which was nice but his exams were unbelievable, they were always curved and unbelievably hard, the final was impossible, chemistry sucks!
Very good professor. Though he wasn't the head professor for the class, he very well could tackle the job.
